abstract.text: Properties that configure the settings for a user. Some elements of this object have a `metadata` property, which includes the following: - `rights`: The calling users permissions to edit this setting (can be `editable` or `read_only`) - `uiHint`: Internally used to build UIs (can be `available` or `hidden`) - `options`: The values supported for this setting (not all settings have this element)

Properties that configure the settings for a user. Some elements of this object have a `metadata` property, which includes the following: - `rights`: The calling users permissions to edit this setting (can be `editable` or `read_only`) - `uiHint`: Internally used to build UIs (can be `available` or `hidden`) - `options`: The values supported for this setting (not all settings have this element)
this user gets supplemental documents when downloading documents.
this user can use a scratchpad to edit information.
this user can create and manage
this user can set the language used in the standard email format for a recipient when creating an envelope.
Vaulting is enabled for the account.
a user can override the default default account setting for the Sign on Paper option, which specifies whether signers can sign documents on paper as an option to signing electronically.
Only Admin users can change this setting.
indicates that this user can send envelope-specific API requests on the account.
The date on which this user record was last modified.
this user is an administrator for the account.
the account can define the routing order of recipients for envelopes sent by using the DocuSign application.
Only SysAdmin users can change this setting.
Indicates the Power Form mode setting for the user: - `none` - `admin` - `user`
this user can create [electronic seal recipients][eseal].  [eseal]: /docs/esign-rest-api/reference/envelopes/enveloperecipients/#seal-recipient

this user can use the signing attachments feature.

this user must view supplemental documents.
Information about the seals associated with this user.
this user can use the bulk send feature for the account.

Sets how self-signed documents are presented to the email recipients. Valid values are:  - `include_pdf`: A PDF of the completed document is attached to the email. - `include_link`: A secure link to the self-signed documents is included    in the email.
Only Admin users can change this setting.
the account can define the routing order of recipients for envelopes sent by using the eSignature API.
Only SysAdmin users can change this setting.

The user ID (GUID) of the user who last modified this user record. This property is read-only.
this user can send envelopes "on behalf of" other users through the API.
the API returns suggested tabs for documents for this user.
When true, daylight savings time is in effect for this user's time zone.
Note referencing the page that modified this user record.
the system notifies this user before applying a matching template.
this user is prohibited from uploading documents during sending.
